{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking paper, large baking or oven tray (45 x 30 cm), ceramic or glass bowl, plastic wrap or kitchen towel, silicone bread mat, rolling pin, pastry brush, oven","id":"r89850","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-PW4SmkIKvQ8\/XZWqZXJU33I\/AAAAAAAAfXM\/a7TFHwISu2Y1veljbXw4A2r7rbMZySPGgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_KEEwxG5KIiD-b4fY.png","title":"Spiced cherry brioche wreath","publishedAt":"2015-12-14T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Brioche"},{"content":"40 g white sugar"},{"content":"330 g full cream milk"},{"content":"30 g fresh yeast, crumbled"},{"content":"80 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces"},{"content":"1 tsp sea salt"},{"content":"650 g baker's flour, plus extra for dusting"},{"content":"1 egg"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Filling"},{"content":"130 g white sugar"},{"content":"¾ tsp ground nutmeg"},{"content":"½ tsp ground cardamom"},{"content":"2 cinnamon quills"},{"content":"2 star anise"},{"content":"3 whole cloves"},{"content":"100 g dried cranberries, plus extra for garnishing"},{"content":"250 g fresh cherries, pitted, plus extra for garnishing"},{"content":"100 g flaked almonds"},{"content":"20 g unsalted butter, melted, for brushing"},{"content":"icing sugar, for dusting"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"12 g","fat":"16 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"79 g","calories":"2169 kJ \/ 516 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Brioche"},{"content":"Line a large baking or oven tray (approx. 45 x 30 cm ) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Place sugar, milk and yeast into mixing bowl and warm <b>2 min\/37°C\/speed 2<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add butter, salt, flour and egg and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then knead <b>3 min\/<b>."},{"content":"Transfer dough into a large ceramic or glass bowl, then cover with plastic wrap or a damp kitchen towel. Leave to prove in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1 hour). Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Filling"},{"content":"Place sugar, nutmeg, cardamom, cinnamon, star anise and cloves into mixing bowl and mill <b>20 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer 3 tablespoons of the spice mixture into a small bowl, then transfer remaining spice mixture into a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C. Transfer proved dough onto a silicone bread mat or floured work surface and shape into a ball. Divide dough into 2 equal portions, then roll out each portion into a long rectangle (50 x 20 cm)."},{"content":"Divide the larger portion of reserved spice mixture evenly between the 2 rectangles of dough."},{"content":"Place 50 g of the dried cranberries, 100 g of the cherries and 40 g of the flaked almonds into the center of 1 rectangle of dough. Using your hands, gently roll the rectangle of dough into a long sausage shape to enclose the filling."},{"content":"Repeat with second rectangle of dough. Reserve remaining cherries and flaked almonds."},{"content":"Place the lengths of dough next to each other, then criss-cross over each other repeatedly to create a two-piece plait."},{"content":"Seal the ends of the plait by pressing the ends of both dough pieces together, then bring the two ends together to create a wreath. Seal the ends of the wreath together and transfer onto prepared baking or oven tray."},{"content":"Brush wreath with melted butter and top with remaining flaked almonds and cherries. Dust wreath with reserved 3 tablespoons of spice mixture, then bake 30-35 minutes (180°C), until brioche is golden."},{"content":"Allow to cool completely, then garnish with extra dried cranberries and fresh cherries, to taste. Dust wreath with icing sugar just before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If cherries are not in season, use jarred Morello cherries (drained) for the filling and top with glacé cherries."],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","2h 20m","10 slices"]}